            <div id="common-scams" class="tab-content active">
                <h3>🚨 Top WhatsApp Scams Targeting Nigerian Businesses</h3>
                <div class="indicator danger">
                    <span>⚠️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Fake Bulk Buyer (Lagos Special):</strong> Scammer claims to be from Lagos/Abuja wanting large quantities. Creates urgency with travel stories. Requests account details immediately.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator danger">
                    <span>⚠️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Government Contract Scam:</strong> Pretends to be government contractor needing supplies urgently. Uses official-sounding language and fake letterheads.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator danger">
                    <span>⚠️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Foreign Buyer Fraud:</strong> Claims to be international buyer. Sends fake payment confirmations from foreign banks that will "take time to reflect."
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator danger">
                    <span>⚠️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Overpayment + Courier Scam:</strong> "Accidentally" overpays, asks for refund to "courier" who will collect goods. Both buyer and courier are same scammer.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="prevention-tips" class="tab-content">
                <h3>🛡️ Nigerian Business Protection Strategies</h3>
                <div class="indicator safe">
                    <span>✅</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>The Lagos Rule:</strong> If someone claims to be from Lagos/Abuja but can't video call or provide verifiable business address, be suspicious.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator safe">
                    <span>✅</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Bank Confirmation Protocol:</strong> Never release goods until your bank confirms payment. Screenshots can be faked easily.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator safe">
                    <span>✅</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>WhatsApp Business Verification:</strong> Only deal with WhatsApp Business accounts for large orders. Personal accounts are red flags.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="indicator safe">
                    <span>✅</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Local Pickup Preference:</strong> For new customers, suggest pickup from your location. Scammers rarely agree to this.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

